"{\"uid\": \"myrepublica.nagariknetwork.com-news-olympics-football-qualifiers-to-be-held-in-nepal\", \"text\": \"Subscribe Now  KATHMANDU, March 27:\\u00a0 Nepal is going to host the first round of the Asian qualifiers of the women's football for the Olympics to be held in 2024 in Paris, France.  Accordingly, the national women football teams of Nepal and Vietnam will participate in the tournament to be organized by All Nepal Football Association (ANFA). Even though Afghanistan and Palestine are also in the group, both withdrew their names leaving only two teams-Nepal and Vietnam to compete for a place in the second round of the qualifiers.  Asian countries are divided into seven different groups. The winning team of each group will advance to the second round. The first round of matches to be held in Nepal will be held on April 5 and 8 at Dasarath Stadium.    Ballot Box Revolt: What RSP's breakthrough victory...  Warning, Threat or Opportunity? Nepal's major part...  Granary in crisis: Water politics leave Madhesh pa...  \\\"China stands ready to work with Nepal to carry forward the traditional friendship, deepen practical cooperation and advance bilateral relations\\\", read the statement.  Building Nepal's Digital Future  Fuel shortages in Nepal: A hidden threat to health a...  Second Innings of Balen and Gagan  Who will become Balen's climate pilot?  Three \\\"S\\\" factors-sulabhata (availability), sangat (peer influence), and siko (imitation)-are driving Madhesh's youth toward drug addiction.<...  Three \\\"S\\\" factors-sulabhata (availability), sangat (peer influence), and siko (imitation)-are driving Madhesh's youth toward drug addiction.<...  ANFA CEO Indraman Tuladhar said the ANFA submitted all necessary documents regarding foreign players' visas to the Ministry of Youth and Sports and the National Sports Council one and a half mon...  Nepal Republic Media Limited \\u00a9 2026.All right reserved  Nepal Republic Media Limited \\u00a9 2024. All right reser